            "question": {
                "text": "Which of the following languages are undecidable? \nNote that 〈M〉 indicates encoding of the Turing \nmachine M. \n\nL1 = {〈M〉|L(M) = ϕ} \n\nL2 = {〈M, w, q〉|M on input w reaches state q in \nexactly 100 steps} \n\nL3 = {〈M〉|L(M) is not recursive} \n\nL4 = {〈M〉|L(M) contains at least 21 members)",
                "images": [],
                "latex": [],
                "tables": []
            },
            "options": [
                {
                    "id": "A",
                    "text": "L1, L3 and L4 only",
                    "images": [],
                    "latex": [],
                    "tables": []
                },
                {
                    "id": "B",
                    "text": "L2, L3 and L4 only",
                    "images": [],
                    "latex": [],
                    "tables": []
                },
                {
                    "id": "C",
                    "text": "L1 and L3 only",
                    "images": [],
                    "latex": [],
                    "tables": []
                },
                {
                    "id": "D",
                    "text": "L2 and L3 only",
                    "images": [],
                    "latex": [],
                    "tables": []
                }
            ],
            "correctAnswer": [
                "A"
            ],
            "solution": {
                "text": "L1 = {〈M〉|L(M) = ϕ} \n\n Emptiness problem for Turing machine is \nUndecidable. \n\nL2 = {〈M, w, q〉|M on input w reaches state q in \nexactly 100 steps} \n\nFor given M, given w, run exactly 100 steps to \ncheck whether q is reachable or not Decidable. \n\nL3 = {〈M〉|L(M) is not recursive)} \\Rightarrow Undecidable. \n\nL4 = {〈M〉|L(M)contains at least 21 members)} \n\n|L(M)| \\ge 21 non trivial property is Undecidable.",
                "images": [
                    "assets/Theory Of Computation/TOC_Undecidability_and_Reducibility_P50_X1369.png"
                ],
                "latex": [],
                "tables": []
            }
        },
