            "question": {
                "text": "Consider the following problems. L(G) denotes the \nlanguage generated by a grammar G. L(M) denotes \nthe language accepted by a machine M. \n\nI. For an unrestricted grammar G and a string w, \nwhether  wL(G). \n\nII. Given a Turing Machine M, whether L(M) is \nregular. \n\nIII. Given two grammars G1 and G2, whether L(G1) \n= L(G2). \n\nIV. Given an NFA N, whether there is a \ndeterministic PDA P such that N and P accept \nthe same language. \n\nWhich one of the following statements is correct?",
                "images": [],
