                "latex": [],
                "tables": []
            },
            "options": [
                {
                    "id": "A",
                    "text": "I and IV only",
                    "images": [],
                    "latex": [],
                    "tables": []
                },
                {
                    "id": "B",
                    "text": "II and III only",
                    "images": [],
                    "latex": [],
                    "tables": []
                },
                {
                    "id": "C",
                    "text": "II, III and IV only",
                    "images": [],
                    "latex": [],
                    "tables": []
                },
                {
                    "id": "D",
                    "text": "III and IV only",
                    "images": [],
                    "latex": [],
                    "tables": []
                }
            ],
            "correctAnswer": [
                "D"
            ],
            "solution": {
                "text": "I. \nGiven a regular expression R and a string w, \nis w  L(R)?  \n\n\nMembership problem for Regular is \nDecidable. \n\nII. \nGiven a context-free grammar G, is L(G) = ϕ? \nEmptines? \n\n\nMembership, finiteness and emptiness \nproblems for CFL are Decidable. \n\nIII. Given a context-free grammar G is L(G) = Σ* \nfor some alphabet Σ? \n\n\nTotality problem CFL is Undecidable. \n\nIV. \nGiven a Turing machine M and a string w, is \n w  L(M)?  \n\n Membership problem for Turing machine is \nUndecidable.",
                "images": [],
                "latex": [],
                "tables": []
            }
        },
